original: Åby, Östergötl. 1., av godsäg. Axel Andersson o. Anna Åström. G. 46 m. Britt Sundin. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 23, jur. kand. i Upps. 29. Tingstjg. i Linköp. domis. 29-32, tjg. i Svea hovr. 32-33, egen adv:verks. i Linköp. fr. 33. V. krigsfiskal v. Livgren: reg., Svea trängkår, Ostgöta luftv:reg. o. Östg. flygflottilj fr. 36. Led. av styr. f. Skandinavbankens Linköp :kont., suppl. i styr. f. A-B Stora Hotellet, f. Lin-köp. Teater A-B m. fl. Tj :man i fl. ordenssällsk. o. klubbar.
translated: Åby, Östergötland. 1st, son of landowner Axel Andersson and Anna Åström. Married in 1946 to Britt Sundin. — Completed high school in Linköping in 1923, obtained a law degree in Uppsala in 1929. Served as a court clerk in Linköping from 1929 to 1932, worked in the Svea Court of Appeal from 1932 to 1933, and established his own law firm in Linköping from 1933. Became a military prosecutor for the Life Grenadier Regiment, Svea Transport Corps, Östgöta Air Warfare Regiment, and Östergötland Air Force Wing from 1936. Member of the board for Skandinavbanken's branch in Linköping, served as a board member for AB Stora Hotellet, the Linköping Theater Company, and others. Also a member of various social clubs and societies.
